# Frontend Development Rules

## Project Structure

- Entry point: [web/src/main.tsx](mdc:web/src/main.tsx)
- Root route: [web/src/routes/\_\_root.tsx](mdc:web/src/routes/__root.tsx)
- Route tree: [web/src/routeTree.gen.ts](mdc:web/src/routeTree.gen.ts) (generated, do not edit manually)
- Config files: [web/package.json](mdc:web/package.json), [web/vite.config.ts](mdc:web/vite.config.ts)
- Global style: [web/src/style.css](mdc:web/src/style.css)
- Query setup: [web/src/integrations/react-query.ts](mdc:web/src/integrations/react-query.ts)

## Code Organization

- Pages/routes in [web/src/routes/](mdc:web/src/routes/)
- Reusable components in [web/src/components/](mdc:web/src/components/)
- Layouts in [web/src/layouts/](mdc:web/src/layouts/)
- API modules in [web/src/api/](mdc:web/src/api/)
- Shared state in [web/src/stores/](mdc:web/src/stores/)
- Query integrations in [web/src/integrations/](mdc:web/src/integrations/)

## TypeScript Conventions

- Keep API/request/response fields in `camelCase`.
- Reuse module types under `web/src/api/<module>/`.
- Avoid redefining API types in page files.

## Component Architecture

- Use functional components with hooks.
- Keep pages as composition/orchestration; move reusable UI to `components`.
- Do not mix unrelated request logic into presentational components.

## State Management

- Use Zustand for shared state (see [web/src/stores/useAuthStore.ts](mdc:web/src/stores/useAuthStore.ts) and [web/src/stores/useLocalStore.ts](mdc:web/src/stores/useLocalStore.ts)).
- Keep state close to usage; avoid unnecessary global stores.

## API Integration

- Place request logic in `web/src/api/<module>/`.
- Do not write raw HTTP calls directly in route/page files.
- Keep module types next to request wrappers, for example [web/src/api/system/user/user.d.ts](mdc:web/src/api/system/user/user.d.ts).
- Keep API contract changes synced with backend and frontend callsites.

## Styling Guidelines

- Prefer Ant Design and Pro Components as primary UI layer.
- Tailwind is for local supplements, not as a replacement UI system.

## Routing

- Use TanStack Router file routes under [web/src/routes/](mdc:web/src/routes/).
- Keep route guards in root route flow (see `__root.tsx`).

## Development Tools

- Development/build entry remains `vp dev` and `vp build` via package scripts.
- `just check` executes frontend lint through `vp lint`.

## File Naming

- Keep naming consistent with existing files in `web/src/`.
- Do not manually edit generated `routeTree.gen.ts`.
